craterdog.collections.primitives

Class Link<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • craterdog.collections.primitives.Link<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the elements in the linked list.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable

    public final class Link<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable
    This class provides an implementation of a link that makes up a doubly linked list. The first element of the list is connected to the last element in the list to make a ring.
    Author:
    Derk Norton

      • removeLinks

        public static <T> void removeLinks(Link<T> firstLink,
                                   Link<T> lastLink)
        This utility method removes a set of links from a linked list, starting with the first link and including the link before the lastLink. Note, that this means the last link is not removed from the list.
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of element encapsulated by the link.
        Parameters:
        firstLink - The first link in the sub chain to be removed.
        lastLink - The link after the last link in the sub chain to be removed.
